Install Android Studio
Open the project
In File Menu → Project Structure → Project, change Project Language Level to 8.0 - Lambdas, type annotations etc.
Connect your device and build











Instructions I took:
--------------------
Follow instructions on : 
https://blog.flexiple.com/build-your-first-android-ar-app-using-arcore-and-sceneform/
HOWEVER; SKIP THE PLUGIN INSTALL STEP, rather add: implementation 'com.google.ar.sceneform.ux:sceneform-ux:1.9.0' to app level gradle.build and classpath 'com.google.ar.sceneform:plugin:1.9.0' to project level one 
Use this object: https://poly.google.com/view/1YE8U35HXsI

Changes you have to apply before the build works:
1.In File Menu → Project Structure → Project, change Project Language Level to 8.0 - Lambdas, type annotations etc.

2.In project level build.gradle, change classpath 'com.google.ar.sceneform:plugin:1.12.0' to classpath 'com.google.ar.sceneform:plugin:1.9.0'



